<h2 id="section-top">Psychology service</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=720">Bradford Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust</a>
</p>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="service-locations clear">
<div class="panel edit-box">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<p class="address">St Luke’s Hospital, Little Horton Lane, Bradford, BD5 0NA<br/>01274 365176</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent615cf61b6735498cbf9fc7867121b953">
</div>
<p>Psychology Services offer psychological assessment and interventions to adults who have a range of health conditions and to children and families in the Child Development Service.  We also provide assessments prior to some medical surgery.</p>
<p>The department has a range of specialist clinicians including Clinical, Child and Health Psychologists, Counsellors and Assistant Psychologists. We are based at St Luke’s Hospital, although people are also seen at Bradford Royal Infirmary and at various places in the community.  Confidentiality is an important aspect of our service and this is discussed with clients in their first session.</p>
<p>If you would like further information about Psychology Services please contact the department between 9.00am and 4.30pm.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
